Another school is in the spotlight for alleged racism. Parents have been protesting outside the German International School in Cape Town, wanting the principal to address them. eNCA's Monique Mortlock has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Another school is in the spotlight for alleged racism. Parents have been protesting outside the German International School in Cape Town, wanting the principal to address them. WATCH | Tensions diffused at Witbank Technical High School According to reports, a teacher told a class that black people are uneducated because they have no role models. The parents say they want transformation at the school. Watch the video above for more details.